{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"eefb4bfc-450a-4c8d-9267-6f001c0d4f05","content":"In .NET MAUI, use the **lifecycle events** API in your `MauiProgram.cs` (or `App.xaml.cs`) via `ConfigureLifecycleEvents`:\n\n```csharp\nusing Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;\n\nbuilder.ConfigureLifecycleEvents(events =>\n{\n#if ANDROID\n    events.AddAndroid(android => android\n        .OnPause(activity => { /* runs on Android pause */ })\n        .OnStop(activity  => { /* runs on Android stop  */ }));\n#endif\n\n#if IOS\n    events.AddiOS(ios => ios\n        .DidEnterBackground(app => { /* runs on iOS background */ }));\n#endif\n});\n```\n\n**Key points:**\n\n- Add `using Microsoft.Maui.LifecycleEvents;`\n- Platform guards (`#if ANDROID` / `#if IOS`) keep each block from compiling on the wrong target.\n- Other events are available too — `OnResume`, `WillEnterForeground`, `OnDestroy`, etc.\n- This is configured in `CreateMauiApp()` inside `MauiProgram.cs`, on the `MauiAppBuilder`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"990088fc-390f-4fd1-a9b4-19292301c3b8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about how to hook into platform-specific lifecycle events in .NET MAUI — specifically Android's OnPause/OnStop and iOS's DidEnterBackground. This is a general knowledge question about .NET MAUI development, not a codebase-specific task.\n\nI can answer this directly from my knowledge.","outputTokens":380,"requestId":"483C:8197A:764B01C:8293E0F:69F3FB02"},"id":"bb798c45-90f6-46ee-8567-3a92f41ee191","timestamp":"2026-05-01T00:59:55.195Z","parentId":"1b454e3d-f0ad-43a9-958f-4a0b91bac02d"}
